about.summary: Adds SQLAlchemy support to your Flask application

name: flask-sqlalchemy
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Flask-SQLAlchemy" %}
{% set version = "2.4.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0c9609b0d72871c540a7945ea559c8fdf5455192d2db67219509aed680a3d45a

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - flask >=0.10
    - sqlalchemy >=0.8.0

test:
  imports:
    - flask_sqlalchemy

about:
  home: http://github.com/mitsuhiko/flask-sqlalchemy
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.rst
  summary: 'Adds SQLAlchemy support to your Flask application'
  dev_url: https://github.com/mitsuhiko/flask-sqlalchemy
  doc_url: http://flask-sqlalchemy.pocoo.org/{{ version }}/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
